  "title": "Conquas Site Supervisor (QAQC)",
  "description": "<h2>Conquas Supervisor (QAQC)</h2><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Manage daily architectural site operations to ensure compliance with CONQUAS standards and project requirements.</p></li><li><p>Handle architectural work scheduling, material requisition, and cost control.</p></li><li><p>Review architectural drawings and coordinate with M&E and Structural teams to resolve any design discrepancies.</p></li><li><p>Conduct regular quality checks and on-site inspections for all architectural works.</p></li><li><p>Oversee sub-contractors and suppliers to ensure work is performed according to specifications and safety standards.</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper site documentation and prepare regular progress reports.</p></li><li><p>Liaise with clients, consultants, and relevant authorities regarding site matters.</p></li><li><p>Undertake any other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the Project Manager.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Possess a Diploma or Degree in Architectural, Building Engineering, or an equivalent qualification.</p></li><li><p><strong>Must be a Certified CONQUAS Site Supervisor.</strong></p></li><li><p>Minimum 2 years of relevant working experience in a similar capacity within the local construction industry.</p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of BCA CONQUAS, Quality Mark assessments, and local safety regulations.</p></li><li><p>Competent in AutoCAD and Microsoft Project.</p></li><li><p>Systematic and organized approach to site supervision and documentation.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Application Process:</strong></p><p>Interested applicants are invited to send their updated resume.<br /><br />Please include the following details:</p><ul><li><p>Reason for leaving past and current employment.</p></li><li><p>Last drawn and expected salary.</p></li><li><p>Earliest available start date or notice period.</p></li></ul>",
